               Covariances, BNL, July 2011                        4243 1451
Covariances from COMMARA-2.0 were adopted for the Mo isotopes.    4243 1451
Here, new sets of covariances were obtained at BNL in 2010 using  4243 1451
the kernel approach in the resonance region and EMPIRE/KALMAN     4243 1451
analysis of experimental data in the fast neutron region.         4243 1451
Dispersion analysis of the evaluated libraries does not bring     4243 1451
much insight since all major libraries are virtually identical.   4243 1451
Only ROSFOND differs from other major libraries suggesting 15%    4243 1451
uncertainty for elastic above 1 MeV and 50% for capture above     4243 1451
10 MeV. The isotopic data are available for total, elastic and    4243 1451
capture so there was no need to resort to elemental measurements. 4243 1451
The EMPIRE/KALMAN analysis was performed using "nuisance"         4243 1451
parameters scaling total and reaction cross sections to account   4243 1451
for systematic uncertainties and meet dispersion guidelines.      4243 1451
